    slug: "roshni",
    description: `Roshni (Light) is an Urdu-language Islamic book whose title symbolizes the illumination that Islamic knowledge brings to a believer's heart and mind. The book is structured as a collection of Islamic teachings, wisdom, and spiritual guidance designed to dispel the darkness of ignorance, sin, and spiritual neglect. Drawing from the Quran, hadith, and the works of classical Islamic scholars, Roshni provides readers with a multifaceted exploration of topics that are central to living a faithful and purposeful Muslim life.

The book's opening chapters establish the metaphor of light as it appears in Islamic scripture — Allah as the Light of the heavens and the earth (Surah An-Nur), the Quran described as a light that guides, and the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) characterized as a shining lamp. This thematic foundation sets the stage for the practical and spiritual discussions that follow, linking every topic back to the central idea that true knowledge of Islam illuminates the path of righteousness.

Among the topics covered in depth are the importance of acquiring authentic Islamic knowledge, the dangers of acting upon ignorance in matters of religion, and the responsibility of every Muslim to seek at least the basic knowledge necessary for the correct practice of their faith. The book discusses the methodology of Islamic learning as practiced by the early generations of Muslims — learning from qualified teachers, verifying information through reliable chains of narration, and prioritizing the study of the Quran and hadith above all other sources. Readers will find guidance on selecting trustworthy books and scholars in an era of widespread misinformation.

The book also addresses matters of personal spirituality and character development. Chapters are devoted to the cultivation of Taqwa (consciousness of Allah), the practice of sincere repentance, the importance of maintaining a consistent relationship with the Quran through daily recitation and reflection, and the role of Dhikr (remembrance of Allah) in maintaining spiritual awareness throughout the day. The author provides specific supplications and acts of worship that are proven from the Sunnah for various life situations, making the book a practical reference that readers can turn to repeatedly.

Social and communal responsibilities are not neglected. The book discusses the rights of parents, spouses, children, neighbors, and the broader Muslim community, framing each set of rights as a form of worship that brings light to one's life. The importance of unity among Muslims, the prohibition of backbiting and slander, and the duty of enjoining good and forbidding evil are all addressed with supporting evidence from the Quran and hadith.

Roshni serves as both an inspirational read and a practical Islamic reference. Its accessible Urdu language makes it suitable for readers of various educational backgrounds, from students in madrasahs to working professionals seeking to strengthen their understanding and practice of Islam. The book's emphasis on authentic sources and its avoidance of sectarian extremism give it broad appeal across different segments of the Muslim community, making it a valuable addition to any Islamic home library.`,
    metaDescription: "Roshni is an Urdu Islamic book on spiritual guidance. Covers Quranic light, authentic knowledge, character development, and daily worship practices."
