    slug: "roshni-key-minaar-pashto",
    description: `Roshni Key Minaar (Pashto Edition) is the Pashto-language version of the popular Islamic book series that explores the lives, virtues, and contributions of the companions of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) and other prominent figures in Islamic history. The series title, which translates to "Towers of Light," reflects the author's view that the companions and early Muslim personalities serve as beacons of guidance whose examples continue to illuminate the path for Muslims across generations. This Pashto edition makes this valuable content accessible to the large Pashto-speaking Muslim population in Afghanistan, Pakistan, and the wider diaspora.

The book presents biographical accounts of selected companions of the Prophet with an emphasis on extracting practical lessons and moral principles from their lives. Each chapter focuses on a different companion, beginning with their background before Islam, the circumstances of their conversion, their sacrifices and contributions to the early Muslim community, and the qualities that made them exemplary human beings. The accounts are drawn from authentic sources including the major works of seerah, hadith collections, and the classical biographical dictionaries of companion scholars.

Among the companions whose lives are featured in this volume are the early converts who accepted Islam during its most difficult period in Makkah — individuals who endured persecution, economic boycott, and social ostracism for the sake of their faith. Their stories demonstrate the depth of conviction and the strength of character that defined the first generation of Muslims. The book also covers companions who played pivotal roles during the Madinan period, including those who fought alongside the Prophet at Badr, Uhud, and other battles, those who served as scribes of revelation, and those who were entrusted with important responsibilities in the growing Islamic state.

The Pashto translation preserves the scholarly precision and accessible style of the original work while adapting the language to resonate with Pashto-speaking readers. The translators have ensured that technical Islamic terminology is accurately rendered and that the flow of the narrative feels natural in Pashto. Where necessary, brief explanatory notes have been added to clarify cultural or historical references that may be unfamiliar to Pashto-speaking readers.

The book serves multiple audiences within the Pashto-speaking community. For madrasah students, it provides biographical knowledge that is essential for understanding Islamic history. For general readers, it offers engaging stories that inspire faith and moral improvement. For Islamic teachers and khateebs, it provides source material for lectures and sermons. The hardbound or quality paperback edition ensures durability for readers who wish to keep it as a permanent reference in their personal libraries. Roshni Key Minaar in Pashto represents an important effort to make quality Islamic literature available in regional languages, broadening access to authentic Islamic knowledge beyond Urdu and English readerships.`,
