    slug: "sab-se-pyaray-muhammad-rasool-allah-silsila-qasas-ul-anbiya-3030",
    description: `Sab Se Pyaray (Muhammad Rasool Allah) — Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya 30/30 is the final volume (number 30) of the acclaimed Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya (Series of Prophetic Stories), and it is dedicated to Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), whom the title identifies as the most beloved — Sab Se Pyaray. This concluding volume of the thirty-part series holds a special place as it focuses on the greatest of all prophets, the final messenger sent to all of humanity, whose life and mission represent the culmination of the prophetic tradition that began with Prophet Adam and continued through all the prophets covered in the previous twenty-nine volumes.

The book opens by establishing the unique status of Prophet Muhammad among all the prophets — as the Seal of the Prophets (Khatam an-Nabiyyin), the one whose prophethood was foretold in previous scriptures, and the one sent as a mercy to all the worlds (Rahmatan lil-Alamin). The narrative then moves chronologically through the key events of the Prophet's life, beginning with the lineage of the Quraysh and the distinguished ancestry that prepared the way for his coming. The circumstances of his birth, the miracles that accompanied it, his upbringing under the care of Halimah Sa'diyah and later his grandfather Abdul Muttalib and uncle Abu Talib, and the early signs of his future greatness are all narrated with engaging detail.

The book covers the Prophet's youth — his reputation for truthfulness and trustworthiness that earned him the titles As-Sadiq and Al-Amin, his participation in the resolution of the dispute over the placement of the Black Stone in the Ka'bah, and his marriage to Sayyidah Khadijah. The narrative builds toward the pivotal moment of the first revelation in the Cave of Hira and the beginning of his mission as a prophet. The Makkan period is covered with emphasis on the challenges the Prophet faced, the persecution of his followers, the migrations to Abyssinia, the Isra and Mi'raj, and the Hijrah to Madinah.

The Madinan phase — the establishment of the Islamic state, the battles, the treaties, the conquest of Makkah, and the Farewell Pilgrimage — is narrated in a manner that highlights the Prophet's character as a leader, a teacher, a judge, a husband, a father, and a friend. The book emphasizes the moral qualities that made the Prophet the most beloved person to his companions: his kindness, his generosity, his courage, his humility, his sense of humor, and his unwavering commitment to justice.

As the final volume of the series, the book also serves to connect the story of Prophet Muhammad with the stories of all previous prophets covered in the series, showing how his mission fulfilled the promises made to Ibrahim, Musa, Isa, and all the other prophets who came before him. This volume is a fitting conclusion to the comprehensive prophetic narrative that the Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya has built across its thirty installments, making it an essential addition for collectors of the complete series and a moving standalone biography of the Prophet for all readers.`,
    metaDescription: "Sab Se Pyaray Muhammad Rasool Allah is volume 30/30 of Qasas ul Anbiya series. A biography of Prophet Muhammad from birth to Farewell Pilgrimage."
