    slug: "sabar-ka-badla-qissa-syedna-ayyub-silsila-qasas-ul-anbiya-2530",
    description: `Sabar Ka Badla (Qissa Syedna Ayyub) — Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya 25/30 is the twenty-fifth volume of the beloved Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya series, dedicated to the story of Prophet Ayyub (Job — peace be upon him). The title "Sabar Ka Badla" translates to "The Reward of Patience," which is the central theme of Prophet Ayyub's narrative. His story is one of the most powerful and frequently cited examples of unwavering patience in the face of extreme adversity, making it a source of comfort and inspiration for Muslims going through their own trials and difficulties.

The book presents the complete story of Prophet Ayyub as narrated in the Quran and authentic hadith sources. Prophet Ayyub was a wealthy and prosperous man whom Allah had blessed with health, a large family, abundant livestock, and extensive farmland. He was also known for his generosity, regularly feeding the poor and caring for orphans and widows. The book describes the idyllic life that Ayyub enjoyed and his devotion to Allah through prayer and charity, establishing the baseline from which his extraordinary trial would begin.

The narrative then recounts the series of calamities that struck Prophet Ayyub one after another — his crops failed, his livestock perished, his servants were killed, and all his children died in a single disaster. Despite these devastating losses, Ayyub did not curse Allah or complain about his fate. Instead, he fell into prostration and said, "Indeed, adversity has touched me, and You are the Most Merciful of the merciful." The book explores the emotional and spiritual dimension of each loss, helping readers understand the magnitude of what Prophet Ayyub endured and the depth of his patience.

The trial continued with the affliction of a severe illness that affected Prophet Ayyub's body, causing him such pain and discomfort that his skin broke out in sores. The illness was so severe that people abandoned him, and even his wife struggled to care for him. The book narrates the exchange between Ayyub and his wife with sensitivity, showing how even she reached a point of frustration, at which Ayyub made his famous invocation to Allah: "Indeed, I am in distress, so grant me relief." Allah answered his prayer, restoring his health, replacing his family with even more children, and doubling his wealth and property.

The book goes beyond the narrative to extract the practical lessons from Prophet Ayyub's story. It discusses the nature of trials in Islam — that they are a test from Allah, not a punishment, and that those who remain patient are promised a reward without measure. The book addresses how contemporary Muslims can apply the lessons of Sabr (patience) in their own lives when facing illness, financial difficulty, loss of loved ones, or any other form of hardship.

The volume maintains the high production quality and accessible Urdu prose that characterizes the entire Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya series. It is suitable for readers of all ages and serves as an excellent resource for families, madrasah students, and anyone seeking to strengthen their patience and trust in Allah through the inspiring example of Prophet Ayyub.`,
    metaDescription: "Sabar Ka Badla tells Prophet Ayyub's story of patience in volume 25/30 of Qasas ul Anbiya. Covers his losses, illness, and divine restoration."
